óŸOarchive/external_nushell_repo_backup/nushell.github.io/commands/docs/to_json.mdŸ@0fce8b3de28d7ea94b6339c468a285b118d6d2bd6988d7606dbad997de729470Ætitle: to jsonë®Examples⁄ÒOutputs a JSON string, with default indentation, representing the contents of this table.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> [a b c] | to json
[
  "a",
  "b",
  "c"
]

```
Outputs a JSON string, with 4-space indentation, representing the contents of this table.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> [Joe Bob Sam] | to json --indent 4
[
    "Joe",
    "Bob",
    "Sam"
]

```
Outputs an unformatted JSON string representing the contents of this table.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> [1 2 3] | to json -r
[1,2,3]

```
íêê⁄Title: title: to json
Path: Examples
Content:
Outputs a JSON string, with default indentation, representing the contents of this table.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> [a b c] | to json
[
  "a",
  "b",
  "c"
]

```
Outputs a JSON string, with 4-space indentation, representing the contents of this table.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> [Joe Bob Sam] | to json --indent 4
[
    "Joe",
    "Bob",
    "Sam"
]

```
Outputs an unformatted JSON string representing the contents of this table.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> [1 2 3] | to json -r
[1,2,3]

```
